name: Michael Brown
text: Best of the best here. Top notch work to preserve your trophy! Highly recommend giving these gentlemen your business!

name: Larry Bolton
text: He does great work and is very reasonable and he has done work for me

name: Tammy Hulsey
text: They are the best very nice to work with

name: Ed Emerson
text: Shane was recommended to me by a friend and she's an avid duck hunter. This was my daughter's first duck. Nothing prettier than a Wood Duck Drake and, when Shane finished, his work proved that! Amazing talent and definitely worth the wait. While I was there, his wife Heather asked me to look at the many mounts in the shop. All I can say is "WOW"! Shane will be doing a Turkey for me this year for sure! He's the best I've ever seen...I highly recommend him!

name: Jason Thompson
text: Shane is incredibly talented and is the best waterfowl and bird taxidermist in the country. We have had dozens of birds done by Shane over the past 26 years and his meticulous attention to detail is second to none.  I would highly recommend him for any of your waterfowl, bird or turkey taxidermy needs. You will never be disappointed with his work.

name: Jason Thompson
text: Best in the business, hands down! Our dead mount Shane did for us from an Arkansas duck hunt from several years ago.

name: Bryan White
text: Shane is the best on birds anywhere. He has mounted 8 or so ducks for me and they are the best I've seen anywhere

name: Jacob Maples
text: Best waterfowl artist in the south east hands down

name: Crystal Griffith
text: Mike, the owner of Miller's, lets his deer hang for several days with the hide on and you can tell the difference in the meat. It's so tender that you can cut it with a fork. He does many different types of sausages and jerky. His taxidermy work is amazing too! Most definitely worth the drive to go see him and his crew.
